# **Real-Time Chat Application**

This is a real-time chat application built using **Node.js**, **Express**, **Socket.io**, and **HTML/CSS/JavaScript**. It allows users to send and receive messages instantly, with user-specific colored text boxes and a WhatsApp-style background.

---

## **Features**
- Real-time messaging powered by WebSocket using **Socket.io**.
- User-specific styling:
  - Messages from **Person 1** and **Person 2** appear in different colored text boxes.
  - WhatsApp-style chat interface with a customizable background.
- Hosted on a live cloud platform.

---

## **Demo Links**
- **Live Application:** [Chat App on Render]()
- **GitHub Repository:** [Real-Time Chat App](https://github.com/rebaccamin5/COMP2068JSFrameworks)

---

## **How the Demo Application Works**
1. **Choose a User**: 
   - Select between **Person 1** or **Person 2**.
2. **Send Messages**:
   - Type a message and click the **send button** or press **Enter**.
   - Messages appear in uniquely styled text boxes for each user.
3. **Real-Time Updates**:
   - Messages are broadcast instantly to all connected clients.

---

## **Technologies Used**
- **Node.js**: Server-side JavaScript runtime.
- **Express**: Framework for server routing.
- **Socket.io**: Enables real-time, bidirectional communication.
- **HTML/CSS/JavaScript**: Frontend structure, styling, and interactivity.
- **Render**: Cloud platform for hosting the application.
